Fully restored early 2000s Xbox launch series Halo Special Edition console w/ soft mods/hard drive expansion

The console has been fully rebuilt internally with fresh capacitors on the power supply and main board. All thermal compound has been refreshed and a new disk drive belt was installed. 

The console was modded many years ago and kept in a personal collection until it was restored last year. 

The mods were performed in the mid 2000s so they are “correct” for the time period if you collect modded consoles. The other option in that timeframe was the mods done by Team Xecuter but that’s another story. 

The emulators include NES, SNES, Atari, N64 and Sega. 

Everything pictured is included. 2 green controllers, power cord and OEM video cord. No games needed but it will load/play games just fine.
